7 TEMPORARILY EXTEND OPTION TO DECREASE MEDICAID ENROLLMENT
8 BURDEN ON COUNTY DEPARTMENTS OF SOCIAL SERVICES
9 SECTION 1. Section 1.8(a) of S.L. 2023-7, as amended by Section 9(a) of S.L.
10 2024-34, reads as rewritten:
11 "SECTION 1.8.(a) Notwithstanding G.S. 108A-54(d) and in accordance with
12 G.S. 143B-24(b), the Department of Health and Human Services (DHHS) is authorized, on a
13 temporary basis to conclude by June 30, 2025, 2028, to utilize the federally facilitated
14 marketplace (Marketplace), also known as the federal health benefit exchange, to make Medicaid
15 eligibility determinations. In accordance with G.S. 108A-54(b), G.S. 108A-54(f), these
16 eligibility determinations shall be in compliance with all eligibility categories, resource limits,
17 and income thresholds set by the General Assembly."
18
