30 a. The recipient's initial Medicaid eligibility certification period post
31 release.
32 b. Three hundred sixty-five days.
33 (9a) Recipients residing in carceral settings other than prisons and whose Medicaid
34 eligibility has been suspended. Upon the recipient's release from
35 incarceration, the exception under this subdivision shall continue to apply for
