1 The court shall hold an evidentiary hearing no sooner than 60 days after the date the action was
2 filed. All of the following shall apply to the court's determination under this subsection:
3 (1) The medical assistance beneficiary has the burden of proving by clear and
4 convincing evidence that the portion of the beneficiary's gross recovery that
5 represents compensation for the Medicaid claim is less than the portion
6 presumed under subsection (a1) of this section.
7 (2) The presumption arising under subsection (a1) of this section is not rebutted
8 solely by the fact that the medical assistance beneficiary was not able to
9 recover the full amount of all claims.
10 (3) If the beneficiary meets its burden of rebutting the presumption arising under
11 subsection (a1) of this section, then the court shall determine the portion of
12 the recovery that represents compensation for the Medicaid claim and shall
13 order the beneficiary to pay the amount so determined to the Department
14 Department, or designated PHP, in accordance with subsection (a5) of this
15 section. In making this determination, the court may consider any factors that
16 it deems just and reasonable.
17 (4) If the beneficiary fails to rebut the presumption arising under subsection (a1)
18 of this section, then the court shall order the beneficiary to pay the amount
19 presumed pursuant to subsection (a1) of this section to the Department
20 Department, or designated PHP, in accordance with subsection (a5) of this
21 section.
22 (a3) Notwithstanding the presumption arising pursuant to subsection (a1) of this section,
23 the medical assistance beneficiary and the Department may reach an agreement on the portion of
24 the recovery that represents compensation for the Medicaid claim. If such an agreement is
25 reached after an application has been filed pursuant to subsection (a2) of this section, a stipulation
26 of dismissal of the application signed by both parties shall be filed with the court.
27 (a4) Within 30 days of receipt of the proceeds of a settlement or judgment related to a
28 claim described in subsection (a) of this section, the medical assistance beneficiary or any
29 attorney retained by the beneficiary shall notify the Department Department, and any designated
30 PHP, of the receipt of the proceeds.
31 (a5) The medical assistance beneficiary or any attorney retained by the beneficiary shall,
32 out of the proceeds obtained by or on behalf of the beneficiary by settlement with, judgment
33 against, or otherwise from a third party by reason of injury or death, distribute to the Department
34 Department, or designated PHP, the amount due pursuant to this section as follows:
35 (1) If, upon the expiration of the time for filing an application pursuant subsection
36 (a2) of this section, no application has been filed, then the amount presumed
37 pursuant to subsection (a1) of this section, as prorated with the claims of all
38 others having medical subrogation rights or medical liens against the amount
39 received or recovered, shall be paid to the Department Department, or
40 designated PHP, within 30 days of the beneficiary's receipt of the proceeds, in
41 the absence of an agreement pursuant to subsection (a3) of this section.
42 (2) If an application has been filed pursuant to subsection (a2) of this section and
43 no agreement has been reached pursuant to subsection (a3) of this section,
44 then the Department Department, or designated PHP, shall be paid as follows:
45 a. If the beneficiary rebuts the presumption arising under subsection (a1)
46 of this section, then the amount determined by the court pursuant to
47 subsection (a2) of this section, as prorated with the claims of all others
48 having medical subrogation rights or medical liens against the amount
49 received or recovered, shall be paid to the Department Department, or
50 designated PHP, within 30 days of the entry of the court's order.
