1 b. If the beneficiary fails to rebut the presumption arising under
2 subsection (a1) of this section, then the amount presumed pursuant to
3 subsection (a1) of this section, as prorated with the claims of all others
4 having medical subrogation rights or medical liens against the amount
5 received or recovered, shall be paid to the Department Department, or
6 designated PHP, within 30 days of the entry of the court's order.
7 (3) If an agreement has been reached pursuant to subsection (a3) of this section,
8 then the agreed amount, as prorated with the claims of all others having
9 medical subrogation rights or medical liens against the amount received or
10 recovered, shall be paid to the Department Department, or designated PHP,
11 within 30 days of the execution of the agreement by the medical assistance
12 beneficiary and the Department.
13 (a6) The United States and the State of North Carolina shall be entitled to shares in each
14 net recovery by the Department under this section. Their shares shall be promptly paid under this
15 section and their proportionate parts of such sum shall be determined in accordance with the
16 matching formulas in use during the period for which assistance was paid to the recipient.
17 (b) It is a Class 1 misdemeanor for any person seeking or having obtained assistance
18 under this Part for himself or another to willfully fail to disclose to the county department of
19 social services or its attorney and to the Department the identity of any person or organization
20 against whom the recipient of assistance has a right of recovery, contractual or otherwise.
21 (c) (For contingent repeal, see note) This section applies to the administration of and
22 claims payments under the NC Health Choice Program established under Part 8 of this Article.
23 (d) As required to ensure compliance with this section, the Department may apply to the
24 court in which the medical assistance beneficiary's claim against the third party is pending, or if
25 there is none, then to a court of competent jurisdiction in this State for enforcement of this
26 section."
27 SECTION 4.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to
28 Medicaid claims brought by medical assistance beneficiaries against third parties on or after that
29 date.
